{:spec/title "Polylith compliance remediation (pass 2) — fix remaining poly check errors"

 :spec/description
 "Fix all remaining `poly check` errors after the Error 101 interface-bypass
  pass. Structural Polylith fixes only — no behavior changes.

  GROUP 1: Complete interface definitions (Error 103 — 2 sites)
  phase-deployment and phase-software-factory both claim to implement the
  `phase` interface but are missing ~28 functions each. For each missing
  function, either:
  (a) add a pass-through in the component's interface.clj that delegates
      to the same impl as the canonical `phase` component, OR
  (b) restructure so these components extend the phase interface instead
      of claiming to fully implement it (Polylith extension pattern).

  Option (a) is simpler; option (b) is architecturally cleaner if most
  functions genuinely belong to the canonical phase component.

  GROUP 2: Resolve multi-impl interfaces (Error 106 × 6, Error 108 × 1)
  The correct Polylith pattern: each project includes exactly ONE component
  per interface. Different projects swap which implementation they include.

  For `data-foundry` interface (22 components in dev):
    - miniforge project should include ONLY the connectors it actually uses
      at runtime (currently lists 3: connector, connector-auth, connector-retry
      — these three all claim :data-foundry interface, pick one canonical
      per project or rename the interfaces to be distinct)
    - miniforge-core same — pick one connector per distinct concern
    - Development project uses profiles to bundle all variants for testing

  For `phase` interface (3 components):
    - phase-software-factory and phase-deployment should either:
      (a) stop claiming they implement `:phase` and instead extend it with
          their own interfaces (e.g., `:phase-software-factory`), OR
      (b) the canonical `phase` component becomes the only `:phase`
          implementer; specialized phases live as internal impls that
          are composed, not swapped
    - miniforge project includes the factory phase; miniforge-tui includes
      the tui-appropriate phase; etc.

  Use Polylith profiles in development/deps.edn to bundle all variants for
  test runs (:+phase-software-factory, :+phase-deployment, etc.).

  GROUP 3: Complete project definitions (Error 107 × 3)
  miniforge project: add mcp-context-server base
  miniforge-core: add diagnosis, improvement, reliability components
  miniforge-tui: add 10 missing components + 2 missing bases

  Each project's deps.edn needs the missing entries. Verify the actual
  runtime reachability — some may genuinely not be needed and the poly
  check should be suppressed instead.

  GROUP 4: Fix base-to-brick direct dep (Error 112)
  bases/mcp-context-server/deps.edn has `../../components/messages` as
  a direct path. Change to rely on the component's interface-level
  dependency graph like other bases.

  GROUP 5: Clean up warnings (202, 205, 207)
  - Warning 202: Remove missing paths from development project deps.edn,
    or create the missing directories if they should exist.
  - Warning 205: Rename test fixture namespaces or configure poly to
    exclude them from brick scanning.
  - Warning 207: Remove unreachable components from project deps.edn
    (24 + 14 + 13 entries total)."

 :spec/intent {:type :refactor
               :scope ["components/*/src"
                       "components/*/deps.edn"
                       "bases/*/deps.edn"
                       "projects/*/deps.edn"
                       "development/deps.edn"
                       "workspace.edn"]}

 :spec/constraints
 ["Do not change component behavior — only structural wiring"
  "Interface pass-throughs must preserve existing function signatures"
  "Run poly check after each group to verify progress"
  "Run bb test after each group to verify no regressions"
  "Each group should be a separate commit for reviewability"
  "Profiles must not break existing build:cli, build:kernel, or build:tui tasks"]

 :spec/acceptance-criteria
 ["poly check reports 0 errors"
  "poly check warnings reduced to pre-existing items only (not ours)"
  "bb build:cli, bb build:kernel, bb build:tui all succeed"
  "bb test passes without regressions"
  "data-foundry and phase multi-impls live in Polylith profiles"
  "Project deps.edn files declare only reachable components"
  "mcp-context-server base no longer depends on messages via relative path"]

 :spec/workflow-type :canonical-sdlc}
